longBusinessSummary: Diversified Resources Inc. operates as an oil and gas exploration company in the United States. The company holds 100% interests in the Gracia Field that covers 4,600 acres of oil and gas leases located in Las Anima County; and oil and gas leases covering 920 acres in Denver/Julesburg basin. It also owns interests in the HorseshoeÂGallup field, which covers 10,100 acres of oil and gas leases, and 48 producing wells located in San Juan County, New Mexico. The company is based in Littleton, Colorado. On September 5, 2019, the voluntary petition of Diversified Resources Inc. for reorganization under Chapter 11 was converted to Chapter 7. It had filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy on April 30, 2019.
